I've just done a MASSIVE friends cut, basically if I didn't recognize the name I removed it from my list. 

I've got too much to worry about right now without having to worry about who might be possibly on my friends list.

If you are seeing this and would like to be added back leave a comment and give me a good reason.

I put images of myself in this journal that are intimate and personal and choose to share them with those of you who are friends on my journal. 

I do not, however, enjoy getting rude emails or instant messages, if I do get a message from someone that I think is offensive or inappropriate I will not hesitate to remove you from my friends list. 

If I find out that my pictures are anywhere on the internet besides where I have put them I will have to make my screening process much more intense and most likely delete anyone on my friends list who I have not A-met or B-had contact with in conversation about things other than my pictures. 

I am posting this because I have recently been receiving emails from people who apparently know my name, email and have seen my pictures and are being inappropriate and rude. 

I have had to delete my photobucket account because of this and thus any of my pictures on my journal that were hosted there will now be unavailable. I am sorry to those of you who enjoy these pictures and are not involved, however I had no choice. 

I do not want to have to make cuts to my FL, but if it comes to it, I will. 

Please be courteous and think before being an ass. 

I don't mind comments or instant messages that are encouraging or complimenting, as long as they remain appropriate. Please, use your judgment. If you wouldn't say it to someone in person, don't say it to me. 

Thank you for your time.

To those of you who plan to add me in the future, you must make some comment and give me a reason to add you. EX: Where you saw me, why you are interested in my journal, etc.
Otherwise you can add me all you like but you will not see anything because all of my posts are friends only except for the few I left open.

When the earth was still flat,
And the clouds made of fire,
And mountains stretched up to the sky,
Sometimes higher,
Folks roamed the earth
Like big rolling kegs.
They had two sets of arms.
They had two sets of legs.
They had two faces peering
Out of one giant head
So they could watch all around them
As they talked; while they read.
And they never knew nothing of love.
It was before the origin of love.

The origin of love

And there were three sexes then,
One that looked like two men
Glued up back to back,
Called the children of the sun.
And similar in shape and girth
Were the children of the earth.
They looked like two girls
Rolled up in one.
And the children of the moon
Were like a fork shoved on a spoon.
They were part sun, part earth
Part daughter, part son.

The origin of love

Now the gods grew quite scared
Of our strength and defiance
And Thor said,
"I'm gonna kill them all
With my hammer,
Like I killed the giants."
And Zeus said, "No,
You better let me
Use my lightening, like scissors,
Like I cut the legs off the whales
And dinosaurs into lizards."
Then he grabbed up some bolts
And he let out a laugh,
Said, "I'll split them right down the middle.
Gonna cut them right up in half."
And then storm clouds gathered above
Into great balls of fire

And then fire shot down
From the sky in bolts
Like shining blades
Of a knife.
And it ripped
Right through the flesh
Of the children of the sun
And the moon
And the earth.
And some Indian god
Sewed the wound up into a hole,
Pulled it round to our belly
To remind us of the price we pay.
And Osiris and the gods of the Nile
Gathered up a big storm
To blow a hurricane,
To scatter us away,
In a flood of wind and rain,
And a sea of tidal waves,
To wash us all away,
And if we don't behave
They'll cut us down again
And we'll be hopping round on one foot
And looking through one eye.

Last time I saw you
We had just split in two.
You were looking at me.
I was looking at you.
You had a way so familiar,
But I could not recognize,
Cause you had blood on your face;
I had blood in my eyes.
But I could swear by your expression
That the pain down in your soul
Was the same as the one down in mine.
That's the pain,
Cuts a straight line
Down through the heart;
We called it love.
So we wrapped our arms around each other,
Trying to shove ourselves back together.
We were making love,
Making love.
It was a cold dark evening,
Such a long time ago,
When by the mighty hand of Jove,
It was the sad story
How we became
Lonely two-legged creatures,
It's the story of
The origin of love.
That's the origin of love.

I guess I'm thankful for my wonderful boyfriend, and those who I have met since I've been with him (or as a result of him)

I am grateful for my younger brother and the insane nurturing love I feel for him.

And last I am grateful that I am alive, because it's been a struggle up to this point, and I am sure that it will continue to be so.

Part 1: The Birth of You
Were you a planned baby? Hell no, I was nearly put up for adoption. 
Were you the first? For my mom yeah, for my father, no. 
Who was present at your birth? Couldn't tell ya. 
Were your parents married when you were born? Hah, nope
What is your birthdate? 8/18

Part 2: The Family
Are you parents married or divorced? Neither, they were never together
Are you an only child? Nope
If you have siblings, are you oldest, middle, or youngest? Oldest of the ones I am in contact with
What are your sibling's names? Jessica and Benjamin
Do you have step parents? For sure

Part 3: The Friends
Do you have more than one best friend? I don't consider anyone a "best", so all of my friends... Yes? 
What do you like to do when you are together? Depends on the day/person/money situation
Do you share the same interests? Sometimes, it varies. I wouldn't want all of my friends to be interested in all the same things, that would be boring.

Part 4: Your Personality
How high/low is your self esteem? Depends on when you talk to me, generally pretty low. 
Do you get depressed about things easily? I hate this question. I have suffered from Depression, and may still. So, yes? 
Are you an extrovert (outgoing) or an introvert? A little of both, for the most part I am an introvert, but I do use my voice. 
Are you happy? When I can be
Do you live life to the fullest? I don't know. 

Part 5: Your Appearance
Are you comfortable with the way you look? Sometimes, not generally... but really  who is entirely confident with their physical appearance? 
Describe your hair. Short and red

Part 6: The Past
Were you a strange child? Oh lord, yes. Still am. ;)
Do you have the same friends as when you were a child? For the most part no, but I guess that depends on what you consider Childhood 
Was there anything in your childhood that was traumatizing? Of course. My Mom's first husband and father of my sister was a cocaine addict who would physically and mentally abuse me while my mother worked the night shift at gas stations to keep our family from living on the streets. That is just one of many stories. But.... I turned out more than okay. :)

Part 7: The Future 
What is your ambition? Find a career that will make me happy every day. 
Are you scared of growing old? Not age-wise. Old, I think, is a state of mind. I will never be "old".
Do you want to get married? I think every girl, deep down, has some little voice telling her that she wants to. So, yes, I would like to get married some day. 

Part 8: The Outdoors
Do you prefer indoors or outdoors? Depends on the weather and what I am doing..
Favorite Season. Autumn, the smell and the colors... it is amazing. 
Do you like walking in the rain? Rain, the right rain, can really turn me on. 

Part 9: Food
Are you a vegetarian? I don't have the will power, or the motivation for that matter...
What is your favorite dessert? Don't make me choose! 
What is your favorite restaurant? Anywhere (good) Sushi is served
Are you a fussy eater?Not at all

Part 10: Love
Are you single or taken? *sigh* taken, and amazingly happy. 
If taken who is the lucky guy/girl? That's for me to know.. ;)
Do you think love is the best feeling in the world? Knowing that the person you love feels the same, if not more, and can't take their eyes off of you. 
Do you believe in love at first sight? No.

Part 11: Experiences
What was one of your greatest experiences? I really couldn't tell you...
What was one of the worst? Again... there have been many, I prefer not to single one out..
Have you ever done drugs? I grew up in a small town and hung out with the bad kids.. what do you think? 
Have you ever thought you were going to die? Yes, mainly because of my own self.

It was unbearable.
